code:
```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['US_Gross', 'Worldwide_Gross']]
    plt.scatter(data['US_Gross'], data['Worldwide_Gross'], alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('US Gross')
    plt.ylabel('Worldwide Gross')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of US_Gross and Worldwide_Gross?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['Production_Budget'], bins=20, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['Production_Budget'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Median: {data["Production_Budget"].median():0.2f}')
    plt.xlabel('Production Budget')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Production_Budget?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    data.boxplot(column=['Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating', 'IMDB_Rating'], ax=ax, vert=False, showfliers=True, boxprops=dict(linewidth=2), medianprops=dict(linewidth=2), whiskerprops=dict(linewidth=2), capprops=dict(linewidth=2))
    ax.set_xlabel('Rating')
    ax.set_ylabel('Distribution')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating and IMDB_Rating?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['Running_Time_min'], bins=20, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['Running_Time_min'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['Running_Time_min'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['Running_Time_min'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['Running_Time_min'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Running Time (min)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['MPAA_Rating'])
    rating_counts = data['MPAA_Rating'].value_counts()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(rating_counts.index, rating_counts.values, color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('MPAA Rating')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of MPAA_Rating?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
